---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import FlexComponent from '../../components/Flex.astro';

const usageSnippet = `---
import Flex from '../../components/Flex.astro';

---

<Flex direction="row" gap="md" justify="between" align="center">
  <div>Item 1</div>
  <div>Item 2</div>
  <div>Item 3</div>
</Flex>`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Flex"
  description="Accessible flexbox layout container with semantic HTML options and comprehensive ARIA support."
>
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-base text-slate-100">
      Flex is a powerful layout container that provides a clean API for flexbox
      layouts. Built with accessibility in mind, it supports semantic HTML
      elements and comprehensive ARIA attributes while maintaining WCAG AAA
      compliance.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          direction?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Flex direction. Choose <code>"row"</code>, <code>"column"</code>, <code
            >"row-reverse"</code
          >, or <code>"column-reverse"</code>. Defaults to <code>"row"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          wrap?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Flex wrapping behavior. Use <code>true</code>, <code>false</code>, or <code
            >"reverse"</code
          >. Defaults to <code>false</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          gap?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Gap between items. Choose from <code>"none"</code>, <code>"xs"</code>, <code
            >"sm"</code
          >, <code>"md"</code>, <code>"lg"</code>, <code>"xl"</code>, <code
            >"2xl"</code
          >, or <code>"3xl"</code>. Defaults to <code>"none"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          as?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          HTML element to render. Choose <code>"div"</code>, <code
            >"section"</code
          >, <code>"article"</code>, <code>"aside"</code>, <code>"nav"</code>, <code
            >"main"</code
          >, <code>"header"</code>, or <code>"footer"</code>. Defaults to <code
            >"div"</code
          >.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          ariaLabel?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Accessible label for screen readers when content isn't descriptive
          enough.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Usage</h2>
    <div
      class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
    >
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        Import and use the Flex component to create flexible layouts. The
        component supports all standard flexbox properties with a clean,
        semantic API.
      </p>
      <pre
        class="rounded bg-slate-950/50 p-4 text-sm text-slate-300 overflow-x-auto"><code>{usageSnippet}</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Examples</h2>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Basic Row Layout</h3>
        <FlexComponent
          direction="row"
          gap="md"
          className="p-4 bg-slate-800/50 rounded"
        >
          <div class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Item 1</div>
          <div class="bg-green-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Item 2</div>
          <div class="bg-purple-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Item 3</div>
        </FlexComponent>
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Column Layout</h3>
        <FlexComponent
          direction="column"
          gap="sm"
          align="center"
          className="p-4 bg-slate-800/50 rounded"
        >
          <div class="bg-red-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Header</div>
          <div class="bg-yellow-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Content</div>
          <div class="bg-indigo-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Footer</div>
        </FlexComponent>
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Semantic Navigation</h3>
        <FlexComponent
          as="nav"
          direction="row"
          gap="lg"
          justify="center"
          ariaLabel="Main navigation"
          className="p-4 bg-slate-800/50 rounded"
        >
          <a
            href="#"
            class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors px-3 py-2 rounded focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500"
            >Home</a
          >
          <a
            href="#"
            class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors px-3 py-2 rounded focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500"
            >About</a
          >
          <a
            href="#"
            class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors px-3 py-2 rounded focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500"
            >Services</a
          >
          <a
            href="#"
            class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors px-3 py-2 rounded focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500"
            >Contact</a
          >
        </FlexComponent>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Accessibility</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
        The Flex component is designed with accessibility as a priority:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300 list-disc list-inside ml-4">
        <li>
          Supports semantic HTML elements (nav, section, article, etc.) for
          better document structure
        </li>
        <li>
          Comprehensive ARIA support including aria-label, aria-labelledby, and
          aria-describedby
        </li>
        <li>Role attribute support for custom semantic meaning</li>
        <li>Responsive design that works across all device sizes</li>
        <li>No interference with keyboard navigation or screen readers</li>
        <li>WCAG AAA compliant when used with accessible content</li>
      </ul>
      <div
        class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/10 p-4"
      >
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-200">
          <strong>Best Practice:</strong> Choose the appropriate semantic element
          using the <code>as</code> prop. Use <code>nav</code> for navigation, <code
            >section</code
          > for content sections,
          <code>article</code> for standalone content, and <code>aside</code> for
          sidebar content.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
